    "A dropout 64 of 0.3 (selected through hyperparameter optimization) was added to the last four layers.",
    "Assembly state is defined as a function of the states of its K child assemblies and M additional genes (genes for which the protein products are not present in any descendant assemblies).",
    "Denoting an assembly input vector as I s and an output vector as O s, we have",
    "Here, I s has dimension N × (N × K + M) and O s has dimension N. We define 'in silico activity', a representative singular value for assembly state, as the first principal component 65.",
